ODE SIGNING PRACTICES ARE ONLY AS GOOD AS THE POLICIES BEHIND THEM
Code signing prevents devastating software attacks. Yet signing is often viewed as an afterthought or a tedious extra step. Successful organizations with mature software security rely on strong, written policies to guide signing practices that protect software without slowing or interrupting their CI/CD pipelines. Now, you can read what DevOps experts say should be included in a software signing policy and create your own.

